================================================
DO-WHILE LOOP 
int x=10; 
int y=5; 

while(y>x){
	sout(x); 
	sout(y); 
	x--; 
	y++; 
}

Do-while will run at least one time. Because in do-while loop, we execute the block of code then check the boolean condition. 

do{

	// block of code

}while(boleanCondition); 

